1. Explain what the terminal is in your own words.
The terminal is a tool that lets you type instructions and tell the computer what to do instead of using your mouse/clicking. 

2. What is the major difference between Git and GitHub?
Git is a tool that tracks changes in your code on your computer. GitHub is an online platform that stores your repositories so you can collaborate and share with others. 

What are the steps to fork a GitHub repository?
First you go to the repository, then click "Fork" button, choose which account to fork it, then the copy of the repository will appear in your account.
